Must visit when golfing in Dubai
Sep 2024 • Family
Please see below review I have posted today on google, including a few images.
This was the 4th course we played during our visit to Dubai; and it did not disappoint, especially walking away with 40 points.

The hospitality of the staff was superb, right from Lloyd the manager who went above and beyond to ensure we had a memorable days golfing.

A special mention to Henderson, one of the on course marshal(s), friendly and respectful. Credit where credit is due.

Cleanliness within the changing rooms was absolutely A1.

If you are lucky enough to play here, ensure you eat in the restaurant, all 4 of us thoroughly enjoyed our lunch.

Tricky course, with plenty of water; bring extra balls. fairways and greens were immaculate. Cannot wait to return!

Big thank you to Lloyd, Henderson and the rest of the team.

KR

Daniel Craig

Golf stop off on transit to Mauritius
May 2024 • Couples
We stopped in Dubai for a few days on route to Mauritius and played twice at Dubai creek golf course. With it being a Friday and Saturday you have to sign up to either the 0730 or 1430 shotgun start.

Must say the club is setup well for the amount of people who turn up. Course is in great condition and quite narrow with lots of water and sand. That said I really enjoyed the course and did not find it that challenging.

Food in the restaurant was somewhat disappointing and the drinks somewhat pricey compared to other bars downtown.

Overall worth a visit if you want to knock off another golf course in Dubai.
Written May 25, 2024

Minimised Mini Golf 🤔
Feb 2024 • Family
The mini golf has been minimised from 9 hole to compact 6 hole area that is contained in a plot that is not much bigger than an extended backyard. Beware, the pictures you see on social media, the whole course can be contained in one picture. Earlier the course was also a challenging one making it fun for all in the family. Sadly now, it is only suitable for little children. We chose to enjoy golf in the outdoors with our 10 and 8 year olds but were very disappointed since it got boring as they repeated the easy course twice to complete the slot and unbelievably prices are the same for reduced quality just because the slot is one hour... Who needs an hour when it can be done in less than 30 minutes...
